Affiong’s traditional wedding ❤️❤️❤️❤️
One of my most favorite part of this job apart from watching my brides reaction to their stunning transformation, is I get to watch and also be a part of such beautiful ceremonies like the Akwa Ibom traditional wedding for Affiong and Her husband😊🥰🥰
Nigeria is so so rich in culture and tradition and I must say this is one of my most memorable cultural/traditional wedding with the display of beautiful, vibrant colors, outfits, performances, and joy all around🤩❤️🥰😊

Congratulations Affiong 🥰❤️💐❤️ #bride#akwaibom#calabar#bridalmakeup#makeupartist#newyorkmua#love#wedding#tradition#engagement#nigerianweddinf#bellanaijawedding#weddingdigestnaija#bellanaija

I contemplated on sharing this but here we go…….🤕☺️
Exactly 2 weeks prior to @drsim7 Wedding week, I fell right outside my home on a concrete and broke my knee cap displacing it into 2 pieces 🤕 😣(trigger warning….swipe to see) 
I felt like I was in a bad dream and needed to wake up fast…I couldn’t believe this was happening to me. I had so many plans….EMT came and took me to a trauma hospital where it was confirmed and was told I would need surgery to put the bones together. I was sent back home from the ED the next day while I waited for the hospital to call me and confirm the surgery date. I never heard back from them, I even called them and till this date, no follow up was done @jamaicahospital is trash!!! 

I started looking for alternatives and found a Dr. at @northwellhealth who reassessed and provided me with a surgery date. By this time, it was almost a week after my fall and the swelling and pain had subsided.  I was able to walk with the aid of crutches with mild discomfort. 

I decided I would go ahead and extend my surgery date till after the wedding. Everyone around me knew how excited I was for this wedding…and it would have been very sad for me if I were to not make it. I gathered all my strength and started the wedding week doing makeup from Monday, Thursday, Fri and into Saturday! It was not an easy task and honestly didn’t know how I pulled that week off. 
People who saw me at the wedding walking with a crutch couldn’t believe me and thought I was crazy working with a broken bone 😄😄. I thank everyone for their concern but I was honestly okay doing it.  I believe it was partly due to the excitement I had for this wedding that got me though 😄

Thank you to my girl @arabyssignature for helping me during this time, lifting my legs when needed, Assisting with makeup etc I couldn’t have done this without you!

I had a successful surgery on Monday and now I am on the road to recovery. I will be back with my heels 👠 on soon to testify to God’s goodness as this could have been worse. 🙏🏽

Life throws curve balls our way when we least expect it and we sometimes don’t know how much strength we have in us until stuff like this happens❤️

Hiring a makeup artist or any other vendor for your wedding day should be a task that needs to be considered seriously. Do not choose only based on hype or social media following. Allow the holy spirit to guide and direct you 🔥🔥🙏🏽

One thing I will tell you is the importance of connecting with a vendor, you should be able to connect with the person you chose as your MUA as he or she would likely be present and be beside you though the whole wedding day. 

Having someone who can be your everything as well as step up for you when needed is one of the qualities you need to be looking at when choosing your MUA. 

A makeup artist can be your therapist, a shoulder to cry on, massager, your stylist, tailor, hype man, feed you, etc…I can go on and on.❤️❤️💃🏽💃🏽
